    "description": "Boehringer Ingelheim India Holdings Services has an exciting opening for a Radiologist at our Thane office. Join a company that values innovation, collaboration, and continuous learning.\n\nAbout Boehringer Ingelheim India Holdings Services:\nBoehringer Ingelheim India Holdings Services is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Administer medications and treatments as prescribed\n• Participate in quality improvement initiatives and clinical audits\n• Collaborate with pharmaceutical representatives and medical suppliers\n• Coordinate with multidisciplinary teams for comprehensive patient management\n• Maintain sterile environments and follow infection control protocols\n• Monitor patient progress and adjust treatment plans accordingly\n• Adhere to NABH/JCI accreditation standards\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Diploma or Degree in Hospitality Management\n• 6-10 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Medical Terminology\n• Proficiency in NABH Standards\n• Proficiency in Telemedicine\n• Proficiency in Diagnostic Skills\n• Proficiency in Patient Care\n• Proficiency in HIPAA Compliance\n• Proficiency in Medical Ethics\n• Proficiency in Health Informatics\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Modern office with recreational facilities\n• Employee stock options (ESOPs) for eligible roles\n• Company-sponsored certifications\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Salary Range: 12 LPA - 25 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Thane, Maharashtra, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Boehringer Ingelheim India Holdings Services!",
